{{BLP sources|date=July 2012}} {{Infobox Governor | honorific-prefix = | name = Gunvor Engström | honorific-suffix = | image = | caption = | order = 36th [[List of governors of Blekinge County|Governor of Blekinge]] | term_start = 2008 | term_end = 2011 | appointed = [[Cabinet of Fredrik Reinfeldt]] | lieutenant = | predecessor = [[Ingegerd Wärnersson]] | successor = | birth_date = {{birth date and age | 1950|12|29}} | birth_place = [[Betul, Madhya Pradesh]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[Sweden|Swedish]] | spouse = | party = | relations = | children = | residence = [[Karlskrona, Sweden]] | alma_mater = [[Stockholm School of Economics]] | occupation = | profession = [[Civil servant]] | religion = | signature = | website = http://www.lansstyrelsen.se/blekinge | footnotes = }}
'''Gunvor Engström''', born December 29, 1950 in [[Betul District|Betul]], [[India]], is Swedish business personality and civil servant.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=105&artikel=4582816|title=Gunvor Engström skyndade på beslut|date=July 1, 2011|newspaper=Sveriges Radio|language=Swedish|accessdate=1 August 2012}}</ref> She led ''Företagarna'', a Swedish association of primarily small- and medium-sized businesses and employers, between June, 2002 and December, 2006. She was appointed [[County governor (Sweden)|County Governor]] of [[Blekinge County]] from 1 September 2008 by the Swedish government, for a period of six years, but resigned in 2011.
Engström has a various background with experiences of companies in private and in public.
She has worked nine years in the Swedish Government Offices.
